('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000041', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 1, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] The ditch and henge were dug, possibly using tools made from ___ (1).', 'deer antlers', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000042', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 2, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] ___ (2) may have been arranged in deep pits inside the circle.', 'timber posts', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000043', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 3, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] Builders used ___ (3) to make sledges and rollers.', 'tree trunks', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000044', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 4, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] ___ (4) pulled them on giant baskets.', 'oxen', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000045', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 5, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] They were brought from Wales by ___ (5).', 'glaciers', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000046', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 6, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] A theory arose in the 17th century that its builders were Celtic ___ (6).', 'druids', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000047', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 7, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] Many experts agree it has been used as a ___ (7) site.', 'burial', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000048', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 8, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the notes. Choose NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS from the passage.] In the 1960s, it was suggested that it worked as a kind of ___ (8).', 'calendar', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000049', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 9, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] During the third phase of construction, sandstone slabs were placed in both the outer areas and the middle of the Stonehenge site.', 'TRUE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000050', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 10, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] There is scientific proof that the bluestones stood in the same spot until approximately 1600 BCE.', 'FALSE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000051', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 11, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] John Aubrey''s claim about Stonehenge was supported by 20th-century findings.', 'FALSE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000052', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 12, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] Objects discovered at Stonehenge seem to indicate that it was constructed by a number of different groups of people.', 'TRUE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000053', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000004', 13, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] Criticism of Gerald Hawkins'' theory about Stonehenge has come mainly from other astronomers.', 'NOT GIVEN', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000054', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 14, 'multiple_choice', 'What point does the writer make about AI in the first paragraph? A) It is difficult to predict how quickly AI will progress. B) Much can be learned about the use of AI in chess machines. C) The future is unlikely to see limitations on the capabilities of AI. D) Experts disagree on which specialised tasks AI will be able to perform.', 'C', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000055', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 15, 'multiple_choice', 'What is the writer doing in the second paragraph? A) explaining why machines will be able to outperform humans B) describing the characteristics that humans and machines share C) giving information about the development of machine intelligence D) indicating which aspects of humans are the most advanced', 'A', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000056', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 16, 'multiple_choice', 'Why does the writer mention the story of King Midas? A) to compare different visions of progress B) to illustrate that poorly defined objectives can go wrong C) to emphasise the need for cooperation D) to point out the financial advantages of a course of action', 'B', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000057', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 17, 'multiple_choice', 'What challenge does the writer refer to in the fourth paragraph? A) encouraging humans to behave in a more principled way B) deciding which values we want AI to share with us C) creating a better world for all creatures on the planet D) ensuring AI is more human-friendly than we are ourselves', 'D', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000058', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 18, 'multiple_choice', 'What does the writer suggest about the future of AI in the fifth paragraph? A) The safety of machines will become a key issue. B) It is hard to know what impact machines will have on the world. C) Machines will be superior to humans in certain respects. D) Many humans will oppose machines having a wider role.', 'C', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000059', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 19, 'multiple_choice', 'Which of the following best summarises the writer''s argument in the sixth paragraph? A) More intelligent machines will result in greater abuses of power. B) Machine learning will share very few features with human learning. C) There are a limited number of people with the knowledge to program machines. D) Human shortcomings will make creating the machines we need more difficult.', 'D', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000060', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 20, 'true_false', '[Write YES / NO / NOT GIVEN] Machines with the ability to make moral decisions may prevent us from promoting the interests of our communities.', 'YES', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000061', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 21, 'true_false', '[Write YES / NO / NOT GIVEN] Silicon police would need to exist in large numbers in order to be effective.', 'NOT GIVEN', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000062', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 22, 'true_false', '[Write YES / NO / NOT GIVEN] Many people are comfortable with the prospect of their independence being restricted by machines.', 'NO', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000063', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 23, 'true_false', '[Write YES / NO / NOT GIVEN] If we want to ensure that machines act in our best interests, we all need to work together.', 'YES', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000064', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 24, 'matching', '[Match to phrase: A=medical practitioners B=specialised tasks C=available resources D=reduced illness E=professional authority F=technology experts] AI currently has a limited role in the way ___ (24) are allocated in the health service.', 'C', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000065', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 25, 'matching', '[Match to phrase: A=medical practitioners B=specialised tasks C=available resources D=reduced illness E=professional authority F=technology experts] Such a change would result in certain ___ (25) not having their current level of control.', 'A', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000066', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000005', 26, 'matching', '[Match to phrase: A=medical practitioners B=specialised tasks C=available resources D=reduced illness E=professional authority F=technology experts] It is therefore important that AI goals are appropriate so that discriminatory practices could be avoided regarding ___ (26).', 'E', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000067', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 27, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] People first referred to Leonardo da Vinci as a genius 500 years ago.', 'NOT GIVEN', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000068', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 28, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] The current climate crisis is predicted to cause more deaths than the plague.', 'NOT GIVEN', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000069', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 29, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] Some of the challenges we face today can be compared to those of earlier times.', 'TRUE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000070', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 30, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] Leonardo da Vinci''s ideal city was constructed in the 15th century.', 'FALSE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000071', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 31, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] Poor town planning is a major contributor to climate change.', 'TRUE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000072', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 32, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] In Renaissance times, local people fought against the changes to Pienza and Ferrara.', 'NOT GIVEN', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000073', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 33, 'true_false', '[Write TRUE / FALSE / NOT GIVEN] Leonardo da Vinci kept a neat, organised record of his designs.', 'FALSE', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000074', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 34, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the summary. Choose ONE WORD ONLY from the passage.] This was to provide better ___ (34) for trade and a less polluted environment.', 'transport', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000075', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 35, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the summary. Choose ONE WORD ONLY from the passage.] They included features such as ___ (35) on the exterior of a building.', 'staircases', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000076', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 36, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the summary. Choose ONE WORD ONLY from the passage.] Leonardo da Vinci''s expertise in ___ (36) was evident in his plans for artificial canals.', 'engineering', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000077', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 37, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the summary. Choose ONE WORD ONLY from the passage.] The design of many cities in Italy today follows this ___ (37).', 'rule', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000078', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 38, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the summary. Choose ONE WORD ONLY from the passage.] While some cities from ___ (38) times have aspects that can also be found in Leonardo''s designs.', 'Roman', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000079', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 39, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the summary. Choose ONE WORD ONLY from the passage.] ___ (39) is one example of a city that was redesigned in the 19th century in the way that Leonardo had envisaged.', 'Paris', 1),
('c1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000080', 'b1800000-0000-0000-0000-000000000006', 40, 'fill_blank', '[Complete the summary. Choose ONE WORD ONLY from the passage.] His ideas are also relevant to today''s world, where building ___ (40) no longer seems to be the best approach.', 'outwards', 1);